 researchers who are new to the economics of addiction and students in a variety of economics and policy courses alike.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aEconomicsxPsychological aspects. 0aSocial policyxEconomic aspects. 0aSubstance abusexEconomic aspects. 0aSubstance abusexGovernment policy. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Social Policy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080478067440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804780674423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804780674.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles